Cuban Health Specialists arrive in South Africa to support efforts to curb the spread of COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa stands at 15,515 with 264 deaths.
The Western Cape has just over 9,000 cases which are almost 60% of the country's infection. READ: SA Lockdown: KZN preparing for level 3 It also has the highest number of COVID-19 deaths at 149, followed by KwaZulu-Natal at 45. Gauteng has recorded 25 deaths. READ: ANC Western Cape wants province to revert to Level 5 lockdown Nearly half of the people who tested positive have recovered. Mpumalanga and Northern Cape are the only two provinces that haven't recorded any deaths. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Health Media Release 17 May... by Travis Richards on Scribd 